Introduction

UP10TION (Korean: 업텐션; Japanese: アップテンション) is a seven-member South Korean boy group under TOP Media. The group originally had ten members: Jinhoo, Kuhn, Kogyeol, Wei, Bitto, Wooshin, Sunyoul, Gyujin, Hwanhee, and Xiao. They made their debut with the mini album, Top Secret, on September 10, 2015.

TOP Media revealed on February 28, 2023, that Lee Jin Hyuk chose not to extend his contract which ends on March 11, and would part ways with the company. The agency also stated that Kuhn, Kogyeol, Bit-to, Sunyoul, and Gyujin would leave as well, but UP10TION would remain active with the seven members left, officially confirming Jinhoo and Wooshin’s exit from the group.

In March 2023, it was confirmed that Hwanhee and Xiao decided to part ways with the company after their participation in Boys Planet.
